<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-088-279 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 085 295</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telecommuting Review: the Gordon Report  August 1 1991 v8 n8p10(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Research summary points out bottom-line benefits offamily-friendly programs. (The Changing Workplace: The FlexibleWorkforce News Digest)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A recent report from The Conference Board entitled 'LinkingWork-Family Issues to the Bottom Line' discusses 'family-friendly'personnel management programs such as flextime and family leaveand points out 'evidence to suggest that work-family programs canimprove a company's bottom line.' The programs studied includedchild care centers, parental leave policies, employee assistanceprograms and flextime.andP;  More than 80 studies are cited in thereport; unfortunately, the research is of uneven quality, althoughthe results are encouraging.andP;  Conference Board members canpurchase copies of the report for $20; the price for non-membersis $80.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Personnel ManagementTelecommutingFlextimeTrendsSociologySocial IssuesConference BoardReports.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>